						               													<description>This game uses a simulation system (&amp;quot;Nav&amp;iacute;os de l&amp;iacute;nea&amp;quot;) to recreate naval combat in the period from 1740 to 1815, both at a tactic and strategic level. In the tactical system players control individual ships on a blue grid. In the strategic system, players control squads on an board showing all the Atlantic.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;WARNING: All game components are in Spanish!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The tactical game used to recreate the naval battle of Trafalgar uses the following sequence:&amp;#10;1. Determine initiative&amp;#10;2. Combat: First, the player with the initiative fires cannons, and then the player without the initiative (although damage is applied simultaneously)&amp;#10;3. Movement: First the player without the initiative, then the one with it.&amp;#10;4. Crew actions and surrender: Boardings, Sinkings and Surenders are resolved.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The strategic game uses another sequence:&amp;#10;1. Initiative&amp;#10;2. Meteorology: Climate and Wind&amp;#10;3. Strategic Movement: Squad composition, Sightings, Persecutions&amp;#10;4. Tactical Movement&amp;#10;5. Adjustment phase: delay of strategic orders.&amp;#10;6. Repairs&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Included in the box are:&amp;#10;-Rigid Gameboard (126 x 64 cm), printed on both sides for tactical and strategic maps.&amp;#10;-60 cardboard figures of the ships that participated in the battle.&amp;#10;-180 sails to be mounted on the ships (plus 24 extras)&amp;#10;-Historical Notes which include a replay of the historical battle.&amp;#10;-Rules of play and 150 cardboard mounted markers.&amp;#10;-60 plastic bases for the ships, a vane, and a 6 sided die.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;More information on www.deltaediciones.com&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
